%pyspark
# Query the check-in data
checkinDF = spark.sql("SELECT checkin_dates FROM checkin")
from pyspark.sql.functions import year, count
# Extract the year from the check-in date
checkinDF = checkinDF.withColumn("checkin_year", year("checkin_dates"))
# Count the check-ins per year
yearlyCheckinCountDF = checkinDF.groupBy("checkin_year").agg(count("*").alias("checkin_count"))
# Show the result
z.show(yearlyCheckinCountDF)

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import hour
# Extract the hour from the check-in date
checkinDF = checkinDF.withColumn("checkin_hour", hour("checkin_dates"))
# Count the check-ins per hour and order by check-in hour
hourlyCheckinCountDF = checkinDF.groupBy("checkin_hour").count().orderBy("checkin_hour")
# Show the result
z.show(hourlyCheckinCountDF)

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import HiveContext
hc = HiveContext(sc)
result = hc.sql("""
SELECT b.city, COUNT(*) AS checkin_count
FROM checkin c
JOIN business b ON c.business_id = b.business_id
GROUP BY b.city
ORDER BY checkin_count DESC
""")
z.show(result)

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import HiveContext
# Create a HiveContext
hc = HiveContext(sc)
# Execute SQL query to rank merchants based on check-in frequency
merchant_ranking = hc.sql("""
SELECT b.name AS merchant_name, COUNT(*) AS checkin_count
FROM checkin c
JOIN business b ON c.business_id = b.business_id
GROUP BY b.name
ORDER BY checkin_count DESC
""")
# Show the result
z.show(merchant_ranking)
